[2
Date: Tue, 29 Dec 1998 09:18:19 -0800
From: Glen Otto <gotto@leland.Stanford.EDU>

>>But what might explain these prairie rodents appearing to be "sick" at
this time?<<
I'm not familiar with the distribution of endemic _Francisella_ in Texas,
but here in California we would certainly add tularemia to the list of
diseases to consider if the child begins to show signs of disease during
the observation period after contact with a "sick" prairie dog.
--
